Responsibilities

Drive sales to achieve company's assigned sales target;
Develop strategy and content for digital marketing & social media platforms across different markets and to evaluate effectiveness of different marketing campaigns;
Perform sales analysis and gather market information for sales and marketing strategies' formulation;
Plan & execute marketing activities for assigned product portfolio to increase brand awareness, expand customer base, engagement and achieve sales target;
Monitor and maintain good relationship with existing distributors to maximize sales and profits;
Proactively develop new distribution channels to ensure continuous business growth and expand market coverage;
Manage internal designers & work closely with third parties for advertisements' production;
Monitoring A&P expenditure & product budget;
Organize and support exhibitions, events & brand activities year-round
Support ad-hoc projects and marketing activities as assigned.

Requirements

University degree holder in Marketing / Health Technology / Nutriology / Biology Chemistry or related discipline;  candidate with science background is preferable
Experience in digital marketing and social media marketing is a must
Creative, detail oriented, outgoing and result-oriented with excellent interpersonal communication skill;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese (Mandarin is an asset);
Able to work under pressure with multi-tasking skill, willing to learn;
High sense of responsibility, mature and self-initiative;
Excellent PC skills;

Interested parties please apply in full resume including current and expected salary by clicking 'Apply Now'. To know more about us, please visit our company website at http://www.healthbank.com.hk.

All information received will be kept in strict confidence and only be used for employment-related purposes.

Responsibilities:
Provide Dietetic services to service users of the DHC Express Scheme,  including direct assessment, treatment, program planning & implementation, be responsible for related documentation, communication & reporting;
Conduct primary health promotion, education talk & provide direct patient education & coaching;
As an active member of the multi-disciplinary team and primary healthcare resource hub to engage related service stakeholder and discipline for primary health & chronic disease management;
Provide professional inputs in service planning and development of the Scheme;
To supervise supporting staff, as required
Requirements:
Bachelor of Science in Dietetics plus internship and on list of Hong Kong Academy of Accredited Dietitian;
Possess 5 years or above post-qualification experience in patient care related practice in dietetic service, preferable both in clinical setting or in community setting;
Good interpersonal and problem-solving skills.
Possess good communication and presentation skills
Proactive, mature and independent; possess good computer literacy
Please send full resume with expected salary and reference no. quoted to Haven of Hope Christian Service, Staff Engagement Department, 7 Haven of Hope Road, Tseung Kwan O, New Territories or via email by clicking "Apply Now", or via Whatsapp no. 6507 8148 (with reference no. quoted at the caption) on or before 5 February 2022. Only short-listed candidates will be notified.


Enquiry: 2703 3227 (Phone); 6507 8148 (Whatsapp).


For details about our organization, please visit www.hohcs.org.hk.


Prospective employees are requested to undergo/submit Sexual Conviction Record Check for work relating to children or mentally incapacitated persons before employment. Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.


